\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well she didn't take much interest but she had definitely conservative }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10370011\charrsid1986722 le
anings}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722  too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Why would that be? Would it be her own independent views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Oh I think so, absolutely, yes, yes. I mean to say, a lot of people would - had to struggle and - to make good and - they thought that the Conservative policy - offered the best chance to people of that kind who were willing to make an effort.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Do you remember your father in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Do you know what party he voted for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh the Conservative party.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 What about your mother - was she still alive in 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 That was the first general election that women could vote in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Would she vote at that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh yes. Yes. She always claimed her rights.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Do you know what party she voted for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 She voted Conservative, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
In some places at that time people felt they risked losing their job or their house if they voted differently to their employers - your father was an employer so this question wouldn't apply to him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well I think my answer to t
hat is that no such cases aver came to may notice. Bolton was a very free and easy place and - people - respected on another's views.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Was your father actually a member of the Conservative party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 He was, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Do you remember him working for the party at elections?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 What sort of things did he do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well he - he used to do some canvassing and committee work - of course he was a member of the town council.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 As a Conservative?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 As a Conservative, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 He did canvass and do committee work for the party for elections?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did he do anything for them at other times, other than election times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well - not really except - such duties as pertained to his membership of the party and - membership of the town council.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 What sort of things would he be doing the year generally for the party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Well - to my mind it was difficult to divorce the two because - the national party depends to a very great deal upon its support from the local parties.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 So in being a member of the town council he was working for the party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes, yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did your mother belong to the party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well I don't know that she did. She was a member of the Primrose League.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did she help your father at all in his political activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 No, not really. Only moral support.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 She didn't do anything at election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 When was your father a member of the town council?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well he was a member for roughly thirty years and he came off in - 1938 I think I was. So he was a member from about 1908.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Do you know which ward he represented - was it always the same one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10370011\charrsid1986722 Yes, he represented - he represented Bradford ward. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Because that was the ward in which he - had had business premis
es, he'd lived in it and he - he still lived a few yards outside the border of it and naturally he put up where he was known. And he was member - remained a member for that ward until he was made an Alderman. Then of course the - change takes place.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did he always get in at the election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes, he never failed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Was he returned unopposed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 No. No, he always fought an election but - it was a foregone conclusion. He was very well known and apparently satisfied the electorate.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 How much time would you say he devoted to this work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Quite a lot of time because - he became chairman of the markets committee which was of course very much in his line and - he was - that committee was responsible for the - town markets - and the weights and m
easures department and with one or another and the officials for one or the other it took up quite a lot of his time but of course it was very easy for him to consult them or for them to consult him with having business premises in the centre of the town.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Would most of his work for the party be done in business hours or out of business hours or would it be fairly balanced?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well it was chiefly in business hours in those days because committee and council meetings were held in the daytime. That's 
been altered since. A lot of the meetings are in the evening now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 So it wouldn't encroach a great deal on his personal time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 No. I wouldn't - I wouldn't draw a distinction - especially with a business of that type which - where the premises were
 open from eight thirty a.m. until eight thirty p.m.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 When your parents were not doing their work how did they spend their spare time - shall we take your father and mother separately?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes. Well - father, political activities as we've said, readi
ng and he was very fond of doing odd jobs in his workshop, he - was very - accomplished do-it-your-self man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 This was a workshop at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes. And of course when his business premises were open from eight thirty to - eight - eight-thirty, eleven
 o'clock on Saturday - so there wasn't a great deal of spare time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did he aim at being on the business premises as much of the time as possible?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 What about your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well she was very fond of sewing and crocheting, embroi
dery and knitting, reading and she was very fond of her plants - she had a greenhouse and - which we all took a - part in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did she have any interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes. She - used to go to meetings at the Sunday school and used to go to lect
ure and concerts, she was a very fond of a visit to the cinema. Oh cinema's were then in the early days. You got a good seat and a cup of tea for sixpence. Somebody at the piano and silent films.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 With whom would she go or would she go on her won?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
She very often went on her own. One of us might go with her if we were available but she was quite - willing to go on her own. Because of course if you go to a cinema and particularly silent cinema of that kind in a way you're better on your own, you can
 appreciate what's going on. She stopped going really when - talkie films came in because she was a little hard of hearing. Although she could read sub-titles quite well she - had a job to catch what was said.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Would eight thirty be the time your father would leave work normally to come home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes, well it got to eight thirty - not earlier. Unless he left for some special purpose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 This evening meal you had was tied in with the time he came home wasn't it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 How many evenings a week would he spend a week at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well he very seldom went out in the evening at all unless it was - he'd some - political meeting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Would they be fairly regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Not often. He might call in at the club on his way home and may have 
- maybe there was no meeting had a - a game of billiards, just one game of billiards. He had to call - he really felt he ought to call in on the club because he was a trustee.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 So did he go there regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 More or less regularly - not often, only - merely to show that he was preserving and interest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Regularly but not frequently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did he ever go to a pub?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 I've never }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10370011\charrsid1986722 known}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722  him to go to a pub unless it was in the way of business or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10370011\charrsid1986722 something}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
 of that kind. He wasn't a drinker - he was not interested. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 The next question is did your mother go too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Certainly not - as I say - as I said before, we were strong }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10370011\charrsid1986722 Wesleyan}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722  - whose creed was neither to touch taste nor handle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did your father take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 He occasionally played a game of howls, and as I say, I've already said, occasional billiards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did he ever attend races or bet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did your father or mother belong to any savings clubs - for clothing or sickness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 No, no, not really - they both had life insurance and - they both had bank account.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 While you were still a child attending school how did you get on with your brother and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Was there any of them that you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Not particularly. In - if anything the younger sister because we were nearer in age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 As a child who did you play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Neighbours and schoolfriends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 With your brother and sisters at all or your younger sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 No - not very much because of course the age gap was rather too large at the younger days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Where did you play?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh on the house premises or maybe in the street or other homes and the adjoining countryside.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 What about the park?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Sometimes because - my - grandfather happened to live opposite the park and - some of my friends lived next door.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 What sort of games did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 -Well in the early days the usual }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10370011\charrsid1986722 children's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722  games, hide and seek and - games of the cops and robbers type. And later of course I was occupied with school football and cricket. Swimming and - and I did quite a fair amount of cycling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 When you were a child what happened if you went home dirty after you'd been playing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Told to get washed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did you get scolded at all or was it just accepted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 I think it was accepted as one of the hazards of childhood.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Were you free to play with anybody you chose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Was there anybody your parents would discourage you from playing with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 No. not really. In fact 
- some of the children I played early - in the early part of the century were still patients of mine when I retired.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did you belong to any youth organisations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well I - when - when I was at school. Not when I was at school. When I left school I became an officer in the Boys Brigade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did you have any special hobbies - did you keep pets or collect anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well we always had a pet cat. I collected stamps - we had a greenhouse and I was - I was very fond of doing odd workshop jobs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 You were a do-it-yourself man as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Yes, yes, yes, from a very early age. In fact, my - the toy I liked best when I was young was something mechanical like the works out of a clock or something of that kind rather than any - toys as such.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did you ever go fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Fishing - yes. My father was concerned in business with a number of fishing club and we used to go at Whitsuntide on an expedition from Bolton which left the Great Moor Street }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12731489\charrsid1986722 sidings}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722  in relays, about four or five trains, because everybody went. It was hol - Whit - it was a holiday at Bolton in those days and they went and fished in the canals round Lancaster and }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10370011\charrsid1986722 Morecambe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 . And we usually left about four o'clock in the morning. By breakfast time I thought it was time to come home. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10370011\charrsid1986722 Anyway we had to continue with this fishing on the canal bank 'til sometime late in the morning when all the catches were weighed in. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Might be anything from two or three ounces - the prize winner to two or three pounds among some thousand or so fishermen. Then we went off into }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10370011\charrsid1986722 Morecambe}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722  - spent the rest of the day there. The trains left fairly early for }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10370011\charrsid1986722 Bolton}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722  - round about half past six - seven o'clock. But if you got to the station anytime after about half past vive they were full of people fast asleep 
going to their early start. And that's my only experience of fishing, I think it turned me against it and now I'm only interested in fish to see them swimming about or on a plate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did you do much walking?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes, I was very fond of walking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Locally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Chiefly locally, yes. Of course Bolton's a good jumping off ground. Might take a - tram or whatever it was to the outskirts and start from there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did you go to any theatres or concerts while you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes. Some trip
s were organized by the school and other trips there were the - we had some very good amateur societies in Bolton and occasionally there's be something at the professional theatre that was worth seeing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 So you went fairly often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well I wouldn't say fairly often - I hadn't time. School took most of my time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 So it was occasional then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Occasionally, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Music hall concerts did you go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Was there a music hall then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh yes, yes, there was a music hall in Bolton - the - there was the Theatre }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10370011\charrsid1986722 Royal}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722  and next door to it was the Grand Theatre. Theatre }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10370011\charrsid1986722 Royal}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722  was a theatre proper and the Grand Theatre was a music hall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did you go there at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes. All the leading artists used to come to Bolton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 And did you go to the cinema?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Yes. Of course those were very cheap in those days. You could do yourself proud for ninepence. Or get a satisfactory seat for sixpence. Or inferior one for tuppence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did your parents give you any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 About how much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well the standard rate in those days was - a penny per week per year of age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Penny per week per year of age?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Of age - per year of age, yes. But of course that was supplemented by various gifts for various reasons.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 You would have extra money in addition for special purposes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes, yes, that was a standard weekly payment which always came in. Could be relied on absolutely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 What did you spend your money on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 To tell you the truth I don't really know. Because I was never fond - very fond of sweets or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Was it possible you saved it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh I did save some. And as I say any special things were usually provided for otherwise.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did anyone outside the home help your mother look after her house or family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 No, except for - what's already been detailed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Your servants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Yes. Sometimes we had a resident maid but the - oh yes. But they weren't very stable in those-days. There's so much other attraction in a place like Bolton. In the way of work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 For about what period would you say you did have a resident maid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Oh I wouldn't like even to hazard a guess at - the moment. It wasn't very long and it - in period of time for any one and in the whole it wasn't - too long. We relied chiefly on the - daily people who were stable.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Can you remember anything about the resident ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well I know one of them was a - a blonde named Hilda and we used to call her the Abbess. Because - because she - she came - she'd 
been - a domestic at a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10370011\charrsid1986722 monastery}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 You can remember her can you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 I can just - I've a vague recollection, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Could you remember any of the others at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes, there's another one - who was absolute }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10370011\charrsid1986722 scarecrow}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 . We had to - dispose of her services.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 When you did have a living in maid where did she sleep and eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Well at the time we had a maid we always had a spare bedroom - she could have. And like the other domestics she used to eat in the morning room before the other meal was
 served and then she was available to - answer doors and telephones and things of that kind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Was there anywhere that she could sit when not working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh yes, she'd sit in the morning room. It was quite a nice room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Was that where she normally spent her free time when she wasn't working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did your mother supervise all the housework personally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did you feel at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12731489\charrsid1986722 ease}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722  with these others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 The others? The first one yes, the second one no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 This was the abbess that you felt at ease with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes. Yes. Yes, she was very pleasant girl but - not very stable and - not }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10370011\charrsid1986722 
real}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 -really - relied on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Do you mean for doing the work and so on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes. Oh integrity was all right it was that she wasn't reall
y very competent. And she'd been used to a different sort of work. In an institution, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 How did the daily domestic and she address each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 I couldn't tell you that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 How did she address members of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh she used to address my mother as Mrs or my father as Mr or - and the children as Mr or Miss Christian name.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 So that her relationship was a little more formal towards you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes, because she'd come when we were grown as the domestic - the domestic help had come when we were infants.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 It was still within the period thought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did you feel that either of your resident maids was interested in you as a person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did your mother give any moral guidance to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 I really don't k
now. They - they both got plenty of that from the church they were both Catholics. Although the second one it didn't seem to go very far. The second one was out very late one night, my mother was getting anxious and she said she was going out to confessio
n. So I rang up the priest and asked him if he'd seen anything of her. He said, oh no, she left ages ago. I said, I thought she must have a lot to confess if she was out until this time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Were they allowed time to do just what they liked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Specific time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well they always had a - an afternoon out. And - they were free to do as they liked unless they were actually required on a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did your mother mind what they did in their free time or what time they came back at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well she felt that they ought to be in at a reasonable time and that - any behaviour outside was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10370011\charrsid1986722 compatible}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722  with common decency.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did anybody in the way of relations, friends or neighbours help in the house at any time? If your mother was ill
 or confined to bed how did she manage - did she need extra help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
No. I don't know that she did, she wasn't a person that had much illness and as I say we always had the domestic help in every day and - there was my oldest sister and the rest of us to do odd little things that were necessary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Do you remember what happened when your younger sister was born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 I don't remember what happened when she was born at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did your parents have relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 How much did they see of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh quite frequently. There was my grandfather and - two aunts. Who were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10370011\charrsid1986722 
spinsters}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722  who lived with him and then - my mother's sister and family were - outside the town but not too far away. And then - my father had more distant r
elatives but they were very close and - they used to visit and we used to visit them. They lived in the town and - at that time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Was the visiting from one household to another }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10370011\charrsid1986722 fairly}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722  frequent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 In the case of all these families?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did your parents have friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Where did they see them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Usually in one home or another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did your mother and father share the same friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 To a very great extent yes, although they - they both had - really
 personal friends but they were so close that - they were shared to some extent between one and the other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Were the friends invited into the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes. oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 How often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well that's difficult - very difficult to say really because - 
there was somebody, one or another, coming in at least once a week. But there was no regular time for - any one of them except that there was one lady who used to come - at this specific time }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10370011\charrsid1986722 wince}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722  a week because she carried on a business and it was her convenient time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Would these friends be invited to have something to eat or drink when they came?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well they usually came to a meal. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10370011\charrsid1986722 
Might call in between with some news or message.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Casually you mean, without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 What about neighbours, were they invited into the home at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Often or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well I wouldn't say they were invited in very often but often called in casually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Would neighbours be offered anything to eat or drink when they came?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Just depended how long they could stay. If they were about at a meal time they'd be invited to share it but otherwise it was usually just a casual visit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did your parents go out themselves to visit friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Both friends and neighbours?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10370011\charrsid1986722 Chiefly}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722  friends - and relatives.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
People often say that in those days they used to make their own amusements - what do you think your parents did when they got together with their friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well it was chiefly 
conversation. Except that one house I remember, the man was a great - what shall I say - lover of any new games that came on the market and he'd quite a collection of these that he wanted everybody to try.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did they have musical episodes as well or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well I only remember them going to the music hall once.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did they use music as a source of entertainment in each other's homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 No, not particular - it was chiefly conversation, and I remember very well my mother being a Strict }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10370011\charrsid1986722 Wesleyan}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722  w
e weren't allowed to have a Sunday paper in the - house despite the fact that she couldn't understand that that paper was printed on Saturday. But - she'd one friend who we visited very frequently had a collection of Sunday papers, and from going in to co
ming out you couldn't get a worked out of mother - she was deep in the News of the World.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Many people divide society into different social classes, in the time before 1918 did you think of some people as belonging to one class and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Not really - in Bolton. Because the relationship was very close. I mean to say employers knew all their work people and addressed them by their Christian names. Visited them in their houses if they were sick very often and the same applied to - the work 
people. The boss would be known as auld John and there'd be young John and - that was the sort of attitude.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 What about the really big concerns - some of the spinning mills for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well - in those days, there were practically all family con
cerns where it applied. The families - were all very well known to all their work people and - vice versa. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10370011\charrsid1986722 
Of course, towards the end of that time some of the family concerns were fading out and - sold - more or less }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8847505\charrsid1986722 clueless}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10370011\charrsid1986722 
 limited companies taking over as the families died out but - mostly in my early years - all the mills were family concerns. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 You see, we had the Marston}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8847505\charrsid1986722 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 s with perhaps the - one of the biggest mill firms. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8847505\charrsid1986722 
The Mages were brewers - well all lived in the town at that time.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did they live fairly well }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8847505\charrsid1986722 distributed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722  in the various areas of the town or were the confined to say Chorley New Road area or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh no. No. The - take the Walker family for instance, the tanners, the father and mother lived in Green Lane and - t
wo sons lived in Green Lane another one lived Chorley New Road and so on. They were spread about. Because - the town building hadn't crept out like it has today and - all the suburbs were pleasant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Would they live mainly in the suburbs rather than in the centre of town?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Well yes, really, although some of them did live in the centre of the town - particularly the - proximal part of Manchester Road. And they lived in - in various styles of opulence. I know, when we lived in R}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12731489\charrsid1986722 u}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 shton Lane next door b
ut one was - Charles Ainsworth the mill owner, it was convenient for him - his mills were - only about a quarter of a mile away and people tended - you see, we hadn't got the transport we've got today and people tended to live near to their business as po
s
sible. One or two of them came to - and go off to work but many of them walked. In fact, when I was at school, on the other side of the twin from Great Lever there where we then lived I used to meet at least half a dozen prominent men walking to their wor
k from the Chorley Road district. Of course people used to walk in those days whereas they don't now. And the motor car hadn't made it's advent to any extent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 So did you not see any different social classes at all then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 You can't draw any hard and fast - distinctions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 If we changed social class and called them groups would you see a distinction of any kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well maybe yes, the people were doing the same sort of thing tended to clique together to some extent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Do you mean by occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 By occup - occupation and similar - what shall I say - financial circumstances. But there was nothing hard and fast about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 You couldn't define any limits at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 No, I couldn't define any limits. I mean to say, the boss would go fi
shing with - one of his men who was interested in fishing and - they'd play bowls with one another and so on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 If one were to try and categorize by finance for instance, financial circumstances, how many different levels do you think there would be?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Well that's very difficult to say because - some of the professional men in those days were earning very, very little and some of the work people were earning a lot. Some of the craftsmen were earning a lot. And - even take the colliers. I knew of one 
family, the man worked in pits but had a towels mill which \{ILLEGIBLE\}
 worked. The men did the heave work when they were not on shift on at the weekends and - financially very well off because the things worked together. The men worked in the pits and sold
 the towels to the pit workers and weaving them at home. All that sort of thing went on you know. Which people don't know about or don't think about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 No. Not really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Were you ever told to show special respect to particular People?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well was - teachers and the clergy and - people of that kind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Was there anybody that you called Sir or Master or Madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well, teachers chiefly and some of the clergy. Those were the people one came into contact with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Do you remember anybody showing respect to your parents in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 I might have added to those other categories elderly people particularly and I certainly remember the young we
re usually quite respectable to their elders generally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 You would call an older person Sir or Madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Possibly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Or you would just be more respectful than to somebody of your own age?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Do you remember if anybody made a special show of respecting your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 I don't remember any special show except the ordinary - they were both getting older in those days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 In the area where you lived who were considered to be the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Again here I think the - civic leaders, the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8847505\charrsid1986722 clergy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 , doctors, leading industrialists, employers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 You've mentioned Ainsworth who lived close to you - I suppose you would come into contact with him would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 What sort of a basis would your relationship be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Oh, a neighbourly basis, he - a word about the weather or how was I getting on at school and so on. And - I know this that - I was - after the period I was wounded and in hospital during the war for some considerable period and he never failed to - 
to call and make enquiries at least once a week. People took an int - took a - a - an interest. And it was the same with the Walker family the tanners. One met them and walked with them if - just like anybody - else and - in fact the - connection and frie
ndships stayed to the present day - one of them - well he was the a son of my generation was my Vice Chairman on Executive Council until a - well about a month ago.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 These people that you said would be the most important in the area - why would they }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8847505\charrsid1986722 be considered}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722  important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well that's difficult to say really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 It }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12731489\charrsid1986722 sounds}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
 as if social status had nothing whatever to do with it - is that right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 I don't think it had really, I think a lot was in - in the general breeding, the way they treated 
people and - possibly their capacity for helping by - financially because they had the money and so on. In fact - on - only this week I heard it regretted at a little gathering of people that - the old types on - on one could rely for charitable purposes 
w
ere dying out. You see, in Bolton we had various things - the Thomasson, on of the big - one of the cotton mill owners. He gave - he was very keen on education and gave a series of scholarships and exhibitions to the town and we'd quite a number of people
 of that type but that's all dying out - you don't get as much of it today as you did in the past. And of course those people who did things for other people were appreciated.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Who did these various groups of people associate with - first of all shopkeepers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Well as I - I've already said, there's very little distinction. Naturally they associated with people who were doing the similar things to themselves because they and a common interest. They might have neighbours who were - doctors or solicitor
s, they might have neighbours who were interested in something like fishing in which they were interested. I think it will depended on common interest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 What about the clergy - who did they associate with as friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well there again - it - in Bo
lton area we had very broad minded clergy, I remember when I was a very small boy one of my father's greatest friends was - A Clement Wood at St Peter and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8847505\charrsid1986722 Paul's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 . Although my father was churchman and my mother was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8847505\charrsid1986722 Wesleyan}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722  and he was a Catholic and he - 
the present building was only just completed. The presbytery hadn't been built. He lived in a house in Houghton Street and that's the first house I ever remember going to on my own without being taken. His housekeeper was a very pleasant friendly person a
n
d very fond of children and always made me very welcome. And then of course my father was associated with quite a number of - of clergy. There was the man who was the - the Vicar of the church he attended and - then there was a succession, two or three su
ccession of priests at St Peter and Paul and the friendship continued which had been present with the original one and so on. Couple of local doctors were very friendly and of course as I say people - all sorts.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did the teachers mix freely with people.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
The teachers - oh yes, yes. There again with common interest they tended to associate - to a great extent with themselves because there were a lot of them. There's a great scope for friendship making with common interests and common times of work. 
But I know both my older brother and older sister were teachers and they often had friends to the house and they were of all types. Not necessarily teacher although some of them were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Would there have been any farmers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Farmers - well, not in - t
he accepted sense I don't think. There were farmers of course but they were chiefly - they were chiefly dairy farmers who produced milk and delivered it. I know there's one family - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8847505\charrsid1986722 particular
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722  friends of my mother's and father's from Deane. In fact, I think the last of them's just died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did they have much opportunity for social contact?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Not a great deal. Very little although the life used to visit us the husband was always too busy but we were always a very welcome at the farm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 You think the employers associated with their work people as freely as with other employers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did they associate with other employers on friendly terms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh yes, yes, yes, yes. I remember we - the Bolton Chamber of trade being formed and they all go
t their heads together. That was a case of common interest which I mentioned before. Although there was such a wide diversification of trades. In fact they were called the Combined Traders when they first started not the Chamber of Trade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 This was including manufacturers as well as shopkeepers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
No. Not the Chamber of Trade. The Chamber of Trade or Combined Trades as it was called were all people who dealt in goods but didn't make them. The people who made them were combined together in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12731489\charrsid1986722 Chamber}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722  or Commerce. And curiously enough recently those two have telescoped together under one office and one secretary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Can you see any difference in the nature of a congregation of a Church of England as Wesleyan church at that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12731489\charrsid1986722 time?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 No, none whatever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 You would have representatives of all the different sorts of people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes. Not only - attending but taking office.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Would you say that there was any more money in evidence in either of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 No. It all depended - it varied with the
 different place of worship - in a different locality. If you've got - place of worship which was attended by some wealthy people who - neighbouring to that church well of course - there was more money there than there was at maybe another church. But I k
n
ow the - the church - near home - there wasn't a great deal of wealth, quite substantial people, at the chapel there's certainly one millionaire who was a very - matter of fact every day sort of man always very friendly and pleasant and at the - another l
ocal chapel was attended by the Walker family, the tanners, who were representative of quite a considerable amount of - wealth. It just varied on the locality - with the locality.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Was there any friction at all between the Roman Catholic Church and the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Always very friendly in Bolton. In fact, the chapel I originally attended and the large Catholic church were across the - the sides of them were across the - opposite one another on a side street. And - the - parsons from both appeared on the
 platforms of the other and there was any - complaint, for instance they both bad boys Brigade bands - the services were at different times and occasionally there was a little bit of - not exactly friction because - one hand would be playing while the ser
vice was going on at the other - and just a -a mention stopped that. In fact I should say they were on very friendly terms. Amongst -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did this apply to the people in the congregation as well as to the clergy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 To a great extent, yes. A very great
 extent. As I say, I was brought up in - predominantly Catholic neighbourhood and had Catholic friends and I always have had. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8847505\charrsid1986722 
And - I remember being - oh very, very small indeed and I was taken by the - one of the lady into the new Catholic church to have a look at it.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Would you say that in the area where you lived all the people had the same standard of living or would be different standards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh well, you always get different standards of living. You mean, people in the same income group - the same work group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Yes, well you always get wide differences there. I can give you a couple of instances if you like. I know of a - two families. - The employment of the man in each case was exactly the same. One family consisted of father, mo
ther a boy and a girl. The house was always very well kept, well }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8847505\charrsid1986722 furnished}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
, a cottage type of house. All modernized. They had a - a modern piano which the father played and the boy became a very competent pianist and the father was organist at a local smal
l place of worship and the mother stayed at home and kept house. Both children were at Grammar schools. The other case - the other case was just the man and his wife. She worked as well as him. They lived in a rented house in what you might call rather an
 inferior district, similar in size to the other but not nearly so well kept or well furnished but they were both drinkers and chain smokers. That shows you what can happen with people the same - work and income group. And it applies wherever you go.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Do you think that either would feel superior to the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Of these people. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Were some families thought of as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Do you remember a distinction between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 No not reall
y. Because the - the distinction in a place like Bolton with its diversity of - types of work is - is very little really. And then there's always the opportunity with - with a diversity of trades of a man - if he's a labourer who wants to get on of changi
ng his job and doing better for himself. Of course in those days there was a - quite a diversity of pay which today has been reversed, I mean to say - a labourer today can get more than a craftsman as far as money goes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did your mother and father have the same attitudes towards people of these different types?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 You've mentioned the possibility of a labourer moving to a different sort of job, was
 it possible for people to move fairly freely from one social }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8847505\charrsid1986722 class}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722  to another
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Oh yes, perfectly freely. I mean to say, we've only to look at certain cases in Bolton. At that time. My father sold his first machine for - weighing out his materials - 
his first weighing machine to - a Mr Edge, the founder of Edge's Dolly Blue and he made his stuff up in the scullery of his house. Of course now that business is - sold out, went from strength to strength - produced two knights and an M.P. - two M.P's and
 a Secretary at the War Office during the war - just shows how people can move up. I've several - quite a number of instances of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Do you remember anybody being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes. Quite a number of people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 What sort of people would they be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well - chiefly people who showed kindness and consideration for other people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Do you remember seeing a policeman round where you lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes, there was one lived locally - there was a little - police station.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did your mother ever say that she'd call the policeman if you were naughty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 How do you think the policeman treated people round about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well he seemed to lead rather remote lonely life. As if he was frightened of mixing too fr
eely. With people he might have to - apprehend or whatever it might be. But his family were quite different, his family were quite - behave quite normally and - the wife and the son and daughter. Two sons and a daughter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 What was his attitude towards offenders?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well I never experienced it, I never - really had any close - view of contact with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Was it a very well behaved area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh comparatively - yes. All sorts of little things happened. Mostly - most - mostly the - anything that was 
taking place out of the ordinary was broken up by the fact that the bobby was coming.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 I wondered if he ever took the law into his own hands and administered punishment on the spot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well I never knew of it if it did happen - probably did, most policemen did in those days. But it wouldn't be noticed because it was usual.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Was your home owned or rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Owned. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Do you remember feeling that your parents had a struggle to make ends meet at any stage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes. In the early days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 What did you think about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 That was a condition of normality - I'd been brought up in it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Were there any times when business was bad and this affected the family income in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh no, not really. A business is bound - to fluctuate and there were no really abnormal fluctuations.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 You wouldn't have to get help from any source then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 You had a horse and trap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Can you tell me who looked after the horse and where it was kept?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh, it was kept at the business premises and we - and we had a carter who looked after it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 You went to Sunday school - was it the Church of England or the Wesleyan?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 The Wesleyan - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Were you given lessons by one of your parents, a tutor or a governess?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
No. Not really lessons but - I did have alphabet blocks and a cardboard clock face with fingers on it - I do remember that. Which I played with myself and asked questions if I wanted to know anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 How old were you when you first started school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh - three year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 What were the school hours when you first started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well they were nine 'til twelve and two 'til four in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 What kind of a school was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 It was a - a mixed - board infants.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 How far away from it were you - how long did it take you to get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh it was only about a quarter of a mile away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did you walk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did anybody go with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes, my mother or father took me the first - two or three times until I got used to it but it was so near that I could go myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did you have your midday meal at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes, oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8847505\charrsid1986722 What did you think about the infants' school?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh I liked it - I was particularly fond of what they called object lessons. They ha
d pict - a picture and they talked about it, might be an animal or something of that sort. I got perhaps a little bit bored because - I was - a little bit more advanced than the - some of the other children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 How did you feel about the teachers there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Well - just an accepted fact - and it's so long ago that I've no feelings particularly and I was so young one way or another. You went to school, you were in a class and there was a teacher, that's about all there was to it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Can you remember whether the teachers emphasized particular things as being important - things like manners or tidiness?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
No, I don't know that they did because classes in those days were very large, I couldn't give you a number but I - I have a vision of a very large class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Were they concerned about you}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12731489\charrsid1986722  being}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722  punctual?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did they bother at all about the way you spoke?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 No. No they didn't. In fact they had a little rhyme which was taught, I forget the actual - the exact words - emphasizing
 punctuality and I - I remember one part of it that - and be at school at two minutes to two. That's about all I remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 If you did something that the teachers disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh they shouted at you or - might be - maybe rapped your knuckle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Were girls punished the same way as boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 For what sort of offences?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh, inattention or talking in class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did your parents show an interest in your work at the infants school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did they ask you what you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did they visit the school at all or meet your teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 No. I don't remember them doing that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did the other children there come from similar types of home to your own on different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well there were all typ
es. All - it was customary in those days to attend the nearest school - there was none of this training about on buses and - other vehicles as there is today. A case of - walking to the nearest school very often we've got to remember that the only public 
transport in - at that time was horse trams. Covering a very limited field.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did the teachers single out some of the children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 No. I don't remember anything of that, there are too many to attend.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Were there any gangs or groups of children in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Not that I remember. In an infants school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did any of the children seem to be left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 No. I - I mean to say considering there's so many children to one teacher the - they couldn't be much differentiation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 You went onto another school afterwards didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 What was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8847505\charrsid1986722 As near as I can remember it was when I was about - four and a half years old, I was a little bit bigger and this was a mixed board
 school, not an infants' school.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 You mean it was a junior school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Was this fairly near as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes. It took about maybe ten minutes - as I was in those days. And I went into a class at that time in preparation, I did not go
 into standard one but they had a sort of preliminary class into which I went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 How long was that for - was that until you were five?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 I don't - I don't remember, I didn't - because I left the school - I wasn't there very long. I may have been - I
 don't think I was there, let me see - five - four and a half, five - I don't think I was there more than about twelve months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well can you remember anything about it? Did you like it and so on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 No, I liked it because it was a bit more ad - it w
as more advanced than the other school. I only - I only remember one teacher and she was - very strict. And she was rather keen on tidiness and attention and punctuality.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did you like her or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh I didn't dislike her. She was rather remote.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 What about punishment in that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh she - she was very free with the cane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 What about the other teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well I never came across any other teachers. I was only there, as I say, a short time and I was in her class and I never had
 another teacher only - maybe - for the odd day if she was absent or something of that kind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did the other children there come from all kinds of homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 All - all kinds of homes. I think we can say that quite safely in those days because there wa
s no means of travel. And people attended the school nearest to where they lived.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 When you left that school was that when you moved house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 When I left that - one, yes. Yes. Yes. In fact I've - I've just made a note here, yes, on removal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 So you went onto another junior school then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Nearer your new home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Well - yes. There wasn't much difference really because the one I left and the one I went to were both further from the new house than I'd been accustomed to going.
 But - I changed schools because there was a neighbour - an older boy who could take me, this longer distance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Was that the only reason for the change?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes, I think I may safely say so.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Was it a similar type of environment and that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
It was a similar type of - similar type of environment yes. only the - I think the - there was more change of teachers - we seemed - I seem to remember more than one teacher and they took - seemed to take more interest in the children. Because I know - qu
ite well remember one of them rewarded - correctly answered questions with a Tom Thumb drop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 There was more reward for good things than punishment for had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes. Yes, Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Was this also a board school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes. And it was about a twenty minute walk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Were punishments similar?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well I don't remember much about any punishment there because - I didn't stay there very long.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 How long did you stay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 I left when I was six years old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 This is your fourth school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes. I might be between six - yes, six plus maybe.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 So you can't really remember very much about that one either?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Can you remember whether your parents were showing an interest in what you were doing there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well yes, but there wasn't very much opportunity in a short time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Where did you go to when you were six or seven then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well - a new school was opened and it was almost directly across the road from where we were living.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Was it a similar sort of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 It was a simi
lar type of school but very much less of course, being new and more what shall I say, suburban, and there were - the department, there was an }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8847505\charrsid1986722 entrance}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722  department and then - a mixed department, and there were children of all ages, from first attending the school until school leaving.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 And this was a board school as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes. Yes. But it - it was a Church of England. It was a - I don't know what you would call it - assisted school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Was there the same sort of environment then or would it be different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
There appeared to be no difference at all except that the - the vicar took an interest in the school. He used to come in two or three times a week and - to recruit choristers and things, that kind of - if he possibly could. Because both the c
hurch and the school were new and naturally the vicar took a big interest in the school and of course the headmaster took an interest in the church. Everybody was making an effort to try to get things going in - a new venture.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 But this wasn't the church that you went to was it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Or did you go to that church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Yes - as I say - as I said previously we were both Church and Chapel. Now this was a new church on our own doorstep - and - sittings were taken at this new church rather tha
n the one we'd previously gone to because a lot of change had taken place, people were moving out of the neighbourhood and so on and - my parents were more interested in their neighbours than in the - distant people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did you find then that the church life was different from the previous church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh no, not really. You couldn't differentiate much between - any two churches or any two chapels or any church and chapel in those days.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 I wondered whether with it being new whether they would be having more social activities or things of that kind than the older church?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 I don't think there was really because - there was always quite a lot going on and churches in those days. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8847505\charrsid1986722 We've got to remember that they were the - purveyors of entertainment and leisure time activity - there weren't any cinemas or anything of that kind.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did the fact that it was a new school make it more attractive?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh much more attractive, yes. New furniture, new building - all very nice and clean and airy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Were the teachers different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Oh yes, the teachers were quite different because of course with a new school with a small - intake really to begin with - there was very much more individual attention. You knew the teachers better and although you were in o
ne teacher's class officially - you were taught by several teachers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did you prefer that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes. Yes. Yes, the variety I think was very helpful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Do you think the teachers themselves were possibly a little more enthusiastic with it being a new school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
I think they were. And - an - I think possibly too they were young. Generally speaking you know, you got the odd one or two who were - older but you got several young ones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 You got the impression that they took a more personal interest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Were they therefore able to devote a little more time to character making?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh yes. I think - I think they were - I - I think they kept a better }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8847505\charrsid1986722 eye}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722  on the children in all respects.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 What sort of punishments did they used?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Well - they - they used to make children stay in after school, but I don't think that was too popular from their own point. And then the headmaster used a cane but I think he was - as far as I remember - was the only person who did. When the pe
ople were very naughty they were sent to the headmaster who caned - them if he thought fit. But as I say the - such a - a more careful eye was kept on individual children that there wasn't very much misbehaviour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did the other children attending the school come from the immediate neighbourhood?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
They came from the immediate neighbourhood and they included the children from - the municipal cottage homes which - to which it was be nearest school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did they mix in freely or was there sort of division felt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
There was no division. The only thing - was that the seniors amongst them were responsible for seeing them to school and seeing them home so - they hadn't much time to play about after school because the seniors were naturally anxious to 
- to get them off back again. And they were all ages and some very nice children. There was really no difference in - in the school between them and anybody else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 I was wondering more about after school hours rather than in school - if friendships developed as freely?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well they couldn't because - they were whisked off home immediately school was over. But otherwise they took a full part in everything.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did you get the impression that any of the other school children tended to look down upon them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 No, not at all. Not at all because there was some of the - they were some of the nicest children in the school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 How long did you stay at that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Until I was nine and then the headmaster - saw my father and he said that I'd been t
hrough the school curriculum and I was wasting me time. And he advised a change to this secondary school - to a fee paying secondary school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Was it the headmaster's initiative that brought this about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes. It was, yes, yes. I remember that quite distinctly. He went to see him and told him I was wasting my time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 So you then went onto Bolton school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 No. No, no, we've not got there yet. Well I left that school when I was nine and I went to what was then called the - Central higher 
- Grade School.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 As a fee paying?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes. The fee of course was very small in those days - I think about three pounds a year covered everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 That was further away for you wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 This is the Great Moor Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 This is the Great Moor Street place, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Which was also a board school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes, it was a - a municipal mixed. It was mixed to the extent that boys and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12731489\charrsid1986722 girls}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722  attended but boys and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12731489\charrsid1986722 girls}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722  were segregated into boys and girls classes. They weren't mixed in class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 How did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Walked. As a rule unless it was very wet - but there was - by - just about that time - just before that time - the electric tram had been - put onto the Great Lever route and - of course it was from door to door - almost. And that was used in wet weather.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 When you walked about how long would it take you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh twenty minutes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did you go on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well usually you went with - school companions. By that time. Of course quite a number of other people were going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Were you still going home for your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did you do that all the time you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Practically all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 What did you think of the Central High Grade school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes, I wasn't - oh abo
ut food, - sometimes I stayed in town, it depended on my parents because the school was within less than five minutes walk of our business premises. Sometimes we - had cooking facilities there or we went out to a restaurant but that was only occasionally.
 
If my mother was at home I went home. The - the school - I - I liked the school of course we - the first year usually you were put in somebody's class but you had other teachers for different subjects. You - responsibility of one teachers for general purp
oses and he may - might take most of the - your classes but you did have other teachers. And conditions of course were more competitive. I didn't care very much for the teacher in whose charge I was the first year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 How was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 He was - he wasn'
t very good tempered and he was very strict and I didn't think he was a very good teacher. Of course the bad temper and the strictness might have been some }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8847505\charrsid1986722 compensation}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722  for his lack of capacity - I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 They were stricter all round were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well he was, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 What sort of - things was he strict about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well chiefly behaviour in class, neglected homework.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did they have these sort of clean and tidiness parades of looking at your shoes and whatnot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 I don't remember much about that. They may have done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 I think they did in some schools?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Yes, yes. Yes, you associate that more with the army. I suppose the army experience completely overshadowed anything of that sort at school really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 What sort of punishments did the teachers use?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh, this man, this first man was very fond of the cane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 More so than the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Was it his regular form of punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes. I'd say yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 What sort of things did the other teachers do?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Oh well, they all possessed canes but they didn't use them to the same extent that he did. The next man I went to when I moved on was a very amiable, very pleasant man and he never used the cane unless there was something very serious and he l
ost his temper and he was most severe. But it was only occasionally. Wasn't regular like the first man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did he have a milder sort of punishment for minor offences?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well there was the usual lines to write and - staying in after school. But there 
again those were very - those were fixed to fit the convenience of the teacher. After I'd been there about six months I took the scholarship examination. - And I got a scholarship - a municipal scholarship so after that I moved up in the ordinary way into
 the - care of this more amiable teacher.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did your parents show much interest in what you were doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Oh yes, they were very interested in what I was doing there and went to the - I don't suppose - know that they went there very much except to the school prizes distribution and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did your mother and father both go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Oh yes, yes. And then - we knew quite a number of the - one way and another, we knew quite a number of the teachers there and - sometimes - my father and I 
and two of them had tea at the restaurant that lay between the business premises and the school. We used to meet there - quite casually because we all used it but if we did meet there - they were there at the same time we always had tea together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Would the children attending that school come from a wider variety of homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well as I say we always had a very wide variety wherever I've been.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 But they would come from different parts of the town?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh they came from different parts of the town be - especially because it was absolutely central. In fact }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8847505\charrsid1986722 its}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
 name was a very good one - Central high Grade school - although - names don't last, people want changes and - while I was there as a matter of fact, it - was promoted - Municipal Secondary sc
hool. What difference that made I - I don't know, only it didn't seem quite so appropriate as the central name.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Were the teachers able to give special treatment to some children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well - I think the answer to that is a qualified no. I don't remem
ber getting any special treatment. And I don't remember anybody else although - the school had a very good record for scholarships and - certainly a large number of the pupils took the scholarship - the scholarship examination and they were guided there, 
I
 mean to say, they weren't necessarily taking a scholarship examination every years while they were eligible because if they got a scholarship - they were more or less given a rest the following year. And then if they were thought possibly good enough to 
take it the year after they took it again to get a better scholarship.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 How did that system work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Well - two years after I gained the scholarship by then I was just - under or just over - just about twelve years old. I took a scholarship examinati
on again. And I was fortunate enough to head the list for the town and got a Thomasson Exhibition which was a valuable exhibition which covered tuition, fee - tuition, fees, books and left - somewhere about thirty pounds a year cash.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Was that for staying on at the Central High Grade School?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Not for going to a different one - for staying on there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 No. no. No, no. That was a - the Thomasson Exhibition, you could attend any school in Bolton on out so long as it was used for sch
olastic purposes. As a matter of fact, some years previously my brother had got one and he went to Manchester Grammar School on scholarship but I chose to go to Bolton Grammar School which had - was a much better school then than it was when my brother we
nt to Manchester I could have stayed on at the school I was in. But the amenities were such at the Bolton Grammar - School that - I chose to take advantage of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 So you went to Bolton School at about twelve?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 At twelve years of age. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 The environment and whatnot there would be rather different wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Yes. I know I - I always - I remember after I got that scholarship at the - Municipal Secondary school I - I didn't do any more schoolwork for the - rest of that year 'til I was el
igible to leave - I was promoted and became what was known as headmaster's mug. Which consisted - which consisted of tidying p the papers in his room and - fetching and carrying for him, either in school or round about the town. So that was really a holid
ay.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Was the expression the headmaster's mug the one that was used?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Yes. Yes. It wasn't used officially of course. But it was known to everybody by staff and children and it wasn't exactly headmaster's - it was Daddy Thornton's mug.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 What was the official definition of this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well - probably hadn't got one. And Daddy Thornton was a little man, he always reminded me of an }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8847505\charrsid1986722 owl}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 . He was very grey and rather wizened with a little wispy bread and he always wore a black scull cap.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 I don't suppose he would take a class would he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
He didn't take classes except he took a - he was very keen on English grammar. And he took an - English grammar class for anybody who could attend in the lunch hour. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8847505\charrsid1986722 
This was - extra curriculum if you wish, but they took this class - and people could take advantage of it. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
And he always got a very good attendance because it - it was thought in some quarters that their progress depended on being seen there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Was that true do you think or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 I don't think
 it was really because I don't think he - I think he was too busy to notice. But this was a service and I - I think a very, very good service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Was this once a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh no, it was more than once a week. I forget how many times, I think it was at least twice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Were there any other special little things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
No, I don't remember anything. Except that - one of the teachers used to play the piano while - after assembly in the morning while people disposed to their classes. And she always played the Bees Wedding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8847505\charrsid1986722 there}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
 any school societies functioning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
No. I don't think - here were any there. Unless amongst some of the - older children of course - the people going up - going there to the age of eighteen and I left when I was twelve.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 The Bolton school - that would be independent grant?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes, Independent Grant - Boys Grammar School.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 How did you get there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Walked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 How long would that take?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Approximately half an hour. And quite a number of us walked from the neighbourhood across }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8847505\charrsid1986722 country}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
 and we picked others up on the way. We could - it was possible to go on two trams but it meant going to the town centre and then out again and it took - not less than five minutes longer on the tram than walking.
 Might be considerable more than five minutes difference if you missed a connection of the trams weren't running very well. So people chose to walk - or cycle. Later on I cycled. Sometimes walked, sometimes cycled. But it was - considerably less distance 
across country than - going on the tram. But it was customary of course for children to walk to school then, not like it is now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 What did you think about Bolton School?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh I enjoyed myself there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Were the teachers different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh very mu
ch different. The - the whole of the staff when I was there were either good Oxford or Cambridge graduates or possibly we might have a French teacher who was wholly French qualified otherwise one with a French and a - an English qualification. The same ap
plied to German. And the headmaster was a modern language expert.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Would you say that there was an emphasis on modern languages even in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Rather than on the sciences?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes. Yes. The - the science was very weak because -
 they hadn't go the equipment and the science teacher was - and ordinary graduate of Manchester. But he happened to be the best teacher in the school. And he stayed there until he retired and was a very well known man in town. But the - the modern languag
es were very good and of course classics were very good and mathematics was good, we had a senior - a senior maths maser. He was - he was hopeless as a teacher but he was very good at answering questions if you were in difficulty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did the teachers there concern themselves much about manners and tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Oh very much, yes, yes. Quite a different - atmosphere. And of course, there again, classes were comparatively smaller and it was possible to oversee everything and then of course - you worked in 
- you had a form master but you - for different subjects you had different people all the time. So you got to know there all very well. In those days of course it was a small school, nothing like it is today. The average number when I was there was a litt
le over two hundred, in fact at one time it got down to about a hundred and ninety plus.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 What sort of punishments did they mete out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh - they were very fond of handing out lines and detention and - corporal punishment maybe by a master or anythi
ng serious sent to the headmaster.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Were your parents able to visit this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh yes, there were - there were quite a lot of social things. There was a hobbies exhibition every year and a pri}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8847505\charrsid1986722 z}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 e distribution, school concerts and various activities. And of course the school had ample playing fields and the swimming bath.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 The amenities would be very much superior to any other school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh yes. Yes, superior to any other school in the district, in fact that was one reason for choosing it 
rather than going where my brother went to Manchester Grammar school, because the amenities were superior to Manchester.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 What about the other children and the sorts of home that they came from - would it be as wide?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Quite as wide. Perfectly wide
 open, because of course the school was sponsored to a very great extent by the first Lord Leverhulme, who in talking about the foundation wanted to provide a school - to which anybody could go and merit without any financial consideration whatever. That 
that would be taken care of. And of course it was with various types of scholarships and exhibitions and various things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Was there free and easy mixing with children from poorer homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh very free and easy - yes, yes. Yes. And it's surprising wh
ere they got to ultimately. I know - take one instance, there's one boy who came from rather a - I should say rather a poor home and he was very shy but he soon got into things and I never saw him after I left school until I was in Manchester University a
nd I met him and he invited me to have a look at his department. He was professor of crystallography. We could find several people of that type you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did the teachers single out any of the children for different treatment from the others there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Well yes, they - if they had some particular bent they - they - they encouraged it. Some people showed a natural bent for one subject or another subject or - for some type of games and there was always some - some master who was willing to push it. Who 
was interested in the same sort of thing. In fact it led to quite a lot of friendships between boys - older boys and masters which continued after school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 The teachers would have more opportunity for giving this sort of attention without disadvantage to the rest of the school community?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 More so than in any other school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Oh yes. Yes, definitely. You see, you've got a comparatively small school with a very good standard - and small classes and - there was a general interest all round.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Were there organized activities - school societies and so on there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did you belong to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 What sort of things did you belong to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well of course there was football and cricket which was more 
or less compulsory and swimming and that - these took quite a long time and then there was a chess club, there was a school library and - it's almost difficult to recollect now what other there were at that time. Of course they've spread and spread and sp
read until now at the present moment at the same school you - you wonder how people have time to do any work. And - the - a - these out of school activities produced quit a lot. You may remember the name Scott }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8847505\charrsid1986722 Taggart}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722  - he went to the Bolton school. John Scott }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8847505\charrsid1986722 Taggart}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722  was a boy there when I was he was younger then I was and - that's where he started playing about with - wireless.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 He went on to textile machinery didn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 No, his father was a textile - yes, yes. Yes. His father was the textile machinist and he done a lot of work }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8847505\charrsid1986722 in}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
 - Germany, and John was born in Germany and lived there 'til he was seven. He came over to this country, he came to the school when he was about ten I should think with a fearful German accent but by that time he'd forg
otten all his German, he had to start and learn German again. But like his father he was keen on mechanical things and he turned his attention not to textile machinery but to wireless. Yes, yes. Yes. I knew them both very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 You told me that you had to go to school on Saturday mornings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 That was at Bolton school wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Was that for formal classes or for some of these sporting activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8847505\charrsid1986722 Oh certain formal classes, of course we had Wednesday afternoon off you know. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Then games were played on Wednesday afternoon and Saturday afternoon. The fixture games with other schools and so on and house matches were played on Wednesday and Saturday afternoons.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 So Saturday mornings were formal classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 How old were you when you left there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Eighteen years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 That was when you left school permanently as it was at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Would you have stayed longer if you'd had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 No, because I had the opportunity and I didn't take it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Was that of your own wishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Of my own wishing. The headmaster did all in his power to persuade me to stay on but I - I felt I was needed in the family business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did he want you to stay on at Bolton school for a further period?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
He wanted me to stay there for twelve months and then to go on to - either Cambridge or Oxford. And in fact - I had several close scholarship which he offered me one of these if I would stay on. And I never took the offer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did you attend any part time education after you finished at Bolton school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Do you think you benefited from attending the particular schools that you did attend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Most certainly, I had a wide 
school experience, the last school I attended a very good one and at that school we were kept up to the mark by taking the Cambridge local examinations every year. One took the prelim and one passed it onto the junior and passed and took the senior and we
n
t on taking the senior every year. Until one left. As matter of fact in my last year of early examinations coming forward which one could take for a bit of variety but they hadn't materialized until after I left. The joke was that I had three Cambridge lo
cal certificates, senior with honours and - the entrance to the University fourteen years later very easy. You see, I - I had the University entrance three times over.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 While you were at school did you do anything regularly as means of earning a little money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well - by the time I left school I was very deeply involved in the family business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Were you involved in it before you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh well before, yes. Because I used to spend a lot of spare time from school - with having long hol
idays I could spend time and - in fact I was, certain classes of goods I was buying - seasonal goods. I was buying them. In fact I was doing what would have been some people a full time job in that as well as being at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Confined to the school holidays or during the rest of the year as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Oh during the year - rest of the year because I - I could go down for an evening or an hour in the evening or - on half days after games I could go down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 How much homework did you get while you were at Bolton school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Well, it depended on how quickly you could do it. Only had to - you had to do your homework because - it was necessary to do that if you were going to get through your examination which you knew was looming ahead once a year. And t
hen the school - another thing the school did it had a general knowledge examination which was taken by everybody, beginning of the winter time and - there were two grades, junior and senior. And everybody had to take this general knowledge examination.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 About how much time were you able to devote during term time to go down to the business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Well that's impossible to say. I never kept a diary of it or - I used to go down when - I felt I needed to go down. Certainly I was there two or three times a week at the - not less than two or three times a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Something like four or five hours a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh at least yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Were you paid at all or given extra pocket money or was it purely voluntary?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 I've forgotten all about that. T
here was no - nothing set about it. I couldn't really tell you. I - because I've always been more interested in work itself than what I got for it - what I ever done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Do you think that taking this interest in the business altered your attitude towards school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Not at all. They were two - two separate things. One was school and one was - you could say, home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8847505\charrsid1986722 You went into the business when you were eighteen fulltime did you?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 What exactly did you do when you first went in?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Well I'd been doing some - some office work - since the time I was twelve. And then I did a certain amount of buying, I mean to say, I - I'd go to - see, we did a lot of importing and exporting and by the time I was - in my early teens I was going to Man
chester with my father and meeting the foreign people. In fact, even before I was twelve and but for winning the exhibition I finally won and went to Bolton school I should have gone and been educated in Germany - I - it was already arranged with - a frie
n
d of my father's and - he wanted me very badly to go to the school his son went to, a boarding school in Germany. So - what would have been the outcome of that I don't know anyway of course - a valuable scholarship in this country was - pit it on one side
 really. It's a curious thing that - while I was at the Bolton Grammar school we got a new young master who'd been teaching in Germany and he'd actually been teaching at this school I would have gone to had I gone to Germany.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 What was special about that school - do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
The school in Germany? Oh it was a - it was a good regular German boarding school and I think the idea was especially on the part of this friend, that it would be very valuable to have an English man associated with his contac
ts in Germany. As a matter of fact it was one sided, he was to import into this country to all his friends and relatives, in fact the Dres}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12731489\charrsid1986722 den}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722  area used to take the whole of our hotel in Manchester where they showed their samples. But they were all Germans.
 And I think he was - rather anxious to get an Englishman in to it. Of course, it was quite interesting, you met a lot of interesting people. I met the - the Marchbanks, Sir Simon and his father and - aunt and - Sir Simon himself as a youngster.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 So you were mainly on the buying side were you in the firm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
At first yes. The buying side and office work. And of course I came into contact with a lot of the customers certainly - in fact I was quite well known to them by the time I got into the - business whole time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Would you work the hours as you've already mentioned as your father's hours - eight thirty to eight thirty? And eleven o'clock on Saturdays?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh yes, in fact I - I used to put a bit of overtime in very often. Stocktaking 'til two o'clock in the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 What sort of meal break did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh about an hour - yes about an hour in the middle of the day and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did you have any holidays at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 With pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well - yes. I say - pay was automatic. No question of a holiday without pay.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Can you remember what you were paid when you first started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 I couldn't remember now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Was it yours to do what you wanted with or did you turn some of it over to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh I used }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8847505\charrsid1986722 to turn}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722  some over. We used to have everything on a business basis.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 How did you get on with the other employees?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh very well indeed. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 About how big a business was it - how many people would be employed?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh not very many - two, three - four - five - six, seven, eight, nine - about a dozen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Were they various ages?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Various ages from school age - to retiring age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 How did your employer treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well of course that's not applicable is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 How much authority had you actually got?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Complete.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Right from early on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Yes, because you see - most of the people he had especially had come into after I was already there and the older ones looked to me rather because my father was on the town council and he was 
very often tied up with that and not there and - they I was somebody to look to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 How did you find the employees?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well - for the most part got on with them very well indeed. There was no bad feelings if anybody wanted to leave - could better hims
elf and the rest of it and it led to lasting friendships, in fact even to this day. In fact it's only last week my sister met one - old ex employee and took her out to tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 What was the pace of work like - were people very busy or very fully occupied or did it vary?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Well of course naturally any - anything like that unless it's a conveyor belt job varies - it's bound to, but - we were mostly kept very busy because we carried a large and very assorted stock which had to be kept in perfect order. An
d there was always some job wanted doing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Would the actual stock keeping part of the job be regarded as really the fundamental part of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes. Your stock had to be - type of stock had to be turned over, certain of it was seasonal and if you hav
e seasonal stock you must not have too much left after the seasons over. So it means keeping in perfect order to find out exactly where you stand. And then some - some items had a very rapid turn over and - it was possible to be without it at the wrong ti
me unless you - looked ahead.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Who was actually responsible for the stock control? Was this something that you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12731489\charrsid1986722 supervised}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722  yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Or did you have a particular member of the staff to do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 I took the overall responsibility for - 
certainly for some things long before I left school but - certain people - one or two people had - charge of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8847505\charrsid1986722 certain}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
 s sections and - it needed a very - couldn't do it all, one person couldn't do it all but - even then needed a careful eye keeping on them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Because of the attention to detail which was required?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did you enjoy the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Is there anything about the way the firm was organized or anything that you think would be interesting to somebody who doesn't know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Oh I don't think so really because we've been into all details of why it existed. But - it - that type of business existed because in those days there wasn't the - well the communication lines there are today before the advent of the motor transport 
and that sort of thing. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8847505\charrsid1986722 
If you remem - I remember - this is perhaps relevant, how - goods were brought to the notice of proprietors of such businesses the travellers came from various firms and whereas as now they'd come with some samples in the boot of a 
motor car they arrived at Bolton station complete in top hat and - either frock coat or morning coat and hired a - a handcart, which several were waiting with elderly men who loaded their baskets of samples, usually marked in wicker baskets because of the
 weight, onto the handcart and this - old man trundles this - hand cart in the wake of the traveller round to his various ports of call. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
And the man who hired them the handcarts in Bolton. This is rather interesting, was the grandfather of the leader of the Halle orchestra. He had this - business, he lent out these hand carts. Quite a big business in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Were all your goods sent by train and arrive by train?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes. Well, yes, by - by train and then the station delivery - horse delivery. Flat
 lorries as a rule. The railway company had two methods of delivery, they had the ordinary flat lorry and then they had a - for light parcels they had a two wheeled van. And these made frequent deliveries. And then there were one or two private firms, in 
f
act I saw a lot of one of them, Suttons who covered the whole country and had depots in various towns. They were a bit cheaper than the railway and - although they made use of rail - to - for long distances, but they would collect your stuff - and consign
 it and collect it at the other end and deliver it. Their place was in - back - back of Victoria }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8847505\charrsid1986722 Square}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722  - Bolton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 You mentioned that there were cooking amenities at the business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Were these available to all who worked there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 What other amenities were there - would you say that the working conditions were quite good?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Oh yes. I think so especially for those days because they had cooking arrangements and a little sitting room and they could go and have their meals if they wished to stay in - that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 How long did you actually stay in the business - from eighteen until you went to University?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well, I stayed in the business from eighteen - from 1912 until 1914 when I joined the Army. You won't want to know anything about that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 What service was it that you were in and what your rank was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Oh I enlisted in the artillery - I was - in 1914 I was - I went to - to serve at Preston, Aldershot, Shorncliffe and Borden. Then I was commissioned and I w
as commissioned to a Territorial Unit in fact I was invited to join them by the Bolton Artillery the same time I was offered a commission in the unit I was in. I joined the Bolton Artillery because I thought I was more use there and served in Southport wi
t
h the third line - up to form the third line in Southport then - and in deference to that or whether the second line would be broken up or we'd go out as a unit it was decided to break up the third line, I went to - Bettesfield Park camp in Shropshire and
 done my Artillery training school, from there I went out to France. Came back to the same place and - with new perfectly well I shouldn't be able to serve abroad again and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 This was when you were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12731489\charrsid1986722 wounded}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 And you went into administration?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 When you'd recovered?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Yes. Yes, I had six months in hospital and then - came back and went back and - went into administrative work. I was on the permanent staff of the number two artillery training school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 You were actually training people you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well curiously enough I was - keeping an eye on people who weren't training really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 What happened when you came out of the Army then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 I went back into the family business. Of course now were - we're getting on now. We're in 1919.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 How long did you stay with it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 I stayed with it - see - until 1928.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Was that when your father died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 No. No. No, as I've already explained, this type of business was a type of business which only existed - relie
d for its existence on lack of - communications. By that time of course the motor car and motor transport had arrived in force. Conditions changed and - the type of business we were in was on its way out and it was a question of deciding whether to make t
w
o separate companies or - a wholesale and a retail company or whether to do the one or the other or whether to give up. As my father was retiring age - and wanted to retire and I - I'd no ties and not likely to have any ties because of my condition - I de
cided to do what I'd always wanted to do and go in for medicine. To retire from the business and go into medicine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 So you went to University in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 1928.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Can you give me just a synopsis of...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 What I got? Yes, yes. Well I got a - the B.Sc., and M.P., C.H.B., M.R.C.S.. L.R.C.P. - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8847505\charrsid1986722 prosecutor}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
 in anatomy in the medical school and did some research in anatomy and physiology. And became friendly with the neuro-surgeon and became a member of his - a part time member of his team. He was naturally 
- because he was interested both in what I was doing in research and he was interested because I had been sent to him at the close of the war and - was - of great interest to him as a case. Then I was house physician, Manchester Royal Infirmary - a house 
surgeon at St Mary's Hospital - the - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8847505\charrsid1986722 obstetric}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722  department St Mary's Hospital - and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8847505\charrsid1986722 gaenacological}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722  department, the City emergency branch. That's all Manchester. I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8847505\charrsid1986722 anaesthetist}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722  at various hospitals in fact, most of the hospitals in Manchester and district. But I always wanted to go into general practice which I ultimately did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 When would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 In 1937.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did you start a general practice in Bolton?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 No, I started - I practiced - I joined - I joined a practice in the Isle of Man. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8847505\charrsid1986722 A pr
actitioner had died, another practitioner who was - a friend of friends of mine - wanted to take over a practice of a practitioner who'd died but couldn't do it on his own and got me to go in with him. And I took charge - of - a boys' public school there 
and we organized the medical service at the school. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Tim Walden just taken it over, owing to it being - short of funds and they gave me a free hand which was - made a very nice job. Anyway I found the Isle of Man rather too parochial and I came back to Bolton and - took over a practice in Bolton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 About how long were you in the Isle of Man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 About twelve months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 And you've been in practice in Bolton ever since?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Ever since - yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Would you have preferred any other type of occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 No. By the way do you want to know anything about what I've done in Bolton or is that sufficient.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well if you'd like to tell me briefly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well I - commenced in general practice, I took over an old established practice in fact the practi
ce of the old family doctor. And - I've done various other jobs. I was medical referee for the Ministry of Pensions and the Ministry of Social Security and I've done quite a lot of - voluntary work. In medicine on the local Medical Committee, Executive Co
uncil and of which I'm now Chairman. Co-opted member of the Health Committee and I was twenty - two years on the hospital Management Committee.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Obviously you belonged to the professional organizations didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh yes, yes, I belonged to the B.
M.A. - British Medical Association and Medical Defence Union and the Bolton District Medical Society and now the Medical Institute. I was Secretary of the Medical Society for about a dozen years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 When you were in the family business did you belong to any organization then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
You mean in the way of a trade union? No. Belonged to an employers association. And the Employers Association was Bolton Combined Traders, afterwards the Chamber of Trade. My father and I were founder members of the - of that organization.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Were you quite active in this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did you hold office?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did you think you as employers and the workers had the same interests or different interests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh I think the same interests. And I was - j
ust at that time - it was only at that time that any move for - what shall I say - shop or warehouse workers to join the trade unions and I was all - I was keen that they should and they should all he members of one union because it made negotiations abou
t
 wages and things very much simpler as you're dealing with one person and there was some sort of a standard - prior to that there was no standard of - wages. Which made it very, very difficult in employing people. A certain amount of poaching went on and 
- I felt it was far better that - employers should be long to a - a negotiating body which could determine a rate of remuneration.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did you feel that there were divisions of interest amongst the workers - between trained workers and other workers - wou
ld you have such a distinction?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh no. No, there was no distinction of that kind. But - there were petty personal difference but of course you get that everywhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Would you say that work has changed your general attitude to life at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 No, I don't think so at all. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 You continued to live at home after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did starting full time work change your relationship with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 No. Well naturally it wouldn't in a case like this. It's not like somebo
dy leaving - the nest and going out to work, I'd been brought up in it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 What about your brother and sisters - was your relationship changed towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Not really but of course by that time - my sister was married of course. She married when I
 was about fourteen and - my brother was - out of Bolton. And - my sister was - and her husband would be in perhaps once a week or we'd be round there once a week and my brother was home for holidays. He didn't actually marry until 1916.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did you spend your Sunday any differently from previously?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 I don't think it made any difference.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 You still went on going to church and Sunday school and such like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes, I said, before - that had thinned down a little bit when I got very much involved in school interests.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did you begin to take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
No, I've got no interest at all in politics except medical politics later on. I - it sickened me with my father's thirty years on the council that I decided that I - I would never be persuaded to - offer myself as a candidate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 You did hold views as to which party you supported though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh yes, definitely yes. Definitely Conservative.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Why in particular did you support the Conservatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Because it appeared to be the party that provided opportunity for individual progress. And recognizing - the effort.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did you vote in elections prior to 19.9?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 And you voted for the Conservative party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes. Yes, I not only voted in elections but I acted as - at the polling booth. I was dragged into that. I was also took part in a census.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Prior to an election do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 No - the ordinary censuses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 The 1911 or a later one?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes - 1911.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 You actually took part in that did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 What did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Well the reason that I took part in it was that - the - chief Registrar was a neighbour, and a friend, and he - he called one day very much upset. It was getting near the time for the election - for the census t
o be taken and there was a certain district he couldn't get anybody to take over. It was popularly known as the worst slum in Bolton. He knew that I knew the district and he said would I possibly oblige him by doing this for him. I said, I don't mind at a
l
l. Because I knew the district intimately, I'd been accustomed to walk through in to school every day for six years and in fact I found it very interesting. And I was made very welcome because most of the people knew me. I had one curious experience, I we
n
t to one house, the furniture appeared to consist of two or three orange boxes and - a boy - a late teenager came to the door all black, he'd come from the pit. He was very co-operative and gave me all the information I wanted and then he said - I don't k
now what they pay you for this job but I wouldn't have it for twenty pound a week. Just shows the various attitudes of people. He thought - I was doing a most awful job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 What general impression did you get about all these various homes that you would go into in this district?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well some of them were very clean and tidy. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8847505\charrsid1986722 
And M always maintained this entailing - the Health Committee and places like that in my lot to serve - people insisted at those meetings in calling places slums and running them down. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
You get some of the finest people in the town in those places. People who work and - keep their - places clean and tidy, spend money on them. It's the - it depends on the percentage of the other sort of people who live there whether their district beco
mes a slum or not. Their morals may not be exactly - High Church - you come to houses with a man and a woman and the children are his, mine and theirs. But on the whole I've always got on with them very well indeed. Because I've known them not only from t
hat time but I've known them is general practice and - I think there's too much running down and not enough - help given.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Going back to the time when you did the census in the district did you feel the people in those houses were in the main happy community?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh quite happy. Happiness doesn't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12731489\charrsid1986722 evolve}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722  from - fancy furniture or even tidy houses - or - or - anything of that kind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did you find any people who were resentful of their condition?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 In fact - no. No. In fact the young collier though
t my job was a lot worse that his. A lot of the people in the so called slums were poor because of bad management. I must say that when I was going to school I found - more waste in those streets than in any others. Sort of chain of events. There's no pro
p
er facilities for keeping anything. They haven't got the brains to budget properly for food or that sort of thing and the result was you could always see whole loaves of bread thrown away in their ash bins because they had the old open ash pit in those da
ys you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 That must have been a very interesting experience for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Were you able to escape from political activities altogether - did your father let you get away without doing anything for him at all?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh yes, yes, yes, because - in - in the first place I was too young then I was too involved in schoolwork.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 So would you say you didn't take part in any political activity at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 The only - the only thing I did, I used to - go for his agendas and papers and very o
ften write his speeches for him. But remained strictly neutral myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 You were a sort of ghost writer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Yes, yes. Having ghosted it for all those years I didn't feel like taking it on myself. I just stuck - stuck in recent years to medical polit
ics - and of course I'm a member of the Health Committee. And I'm not playing to the gallery - I don't often say anything in meetings unless I'm asked. Plenty of people who go to make themselves heard especially with the press present.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 You've told me 
how you spent your spare time with cricket - swimming and cycling and so on and you mentioned that later on after you left school you became an officer in the Boys Brigade. Were there any other spare time activities that you took up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 No. Except that I continued to do a bit of cycling and went walking and that sort of thing. I hadn't very much time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did you go out in the evening at all for pleasure?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 On these sort of things or did you go to something different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Boys Brigade was two evenings a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did you go to concerts or anything like that as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes, concerts and then of course - we started getting cinemas and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did you make any new friends when you started to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well I don't know if I did }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8847505\charrsid1986722 really}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722  because I'd - already quite a wide circle and it wasn't until I moved into a different environment.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did you have any special friends at this time - boys or girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Yes. In fact one of them was here a fortnight ago. He's the father of the leader of the Halle Orchestra. We've had the grandfather.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Was he your one special friend or did you have several?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh no, no, there were - there were about one, two - three - four or five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 What sort of things would you do with them or where would you go with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Well we might go to the cinema together - let's say, we might meet in one another's houses. We might take an afternoon off, a couple of us, and go - cycle to Southport or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did your parents meet your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did they expect to know where you were when you were out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Well I - think it's a matter of - common decency to say where you're going - anything special about knowing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did you have to be home by a particular time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 You said that you had been thinking about the home entertainment aspect?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
Well if I could just - although my brother wasn't much of a musician himself he was - chiefly active at - what shall I say - an elocutionist. He
 was very friendly with people in the entertainment line, one family in particular were - the father was a teacher of music and the family were all musical, they all played some instrument and - musical gatherings were held at this house and the - they we
r
e associated with other people in the musical circles then. They used to go to one another's houses and there was a concert somewhere there every night. And I heard of this because my brother of course used to go with this - one of the members of this fam
ily with this chief personal friend and - if they couldn't find anything for him to do, if they were having a little orchestral evening - they gave him a triangle to play.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Did you ever go to any of them with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Occasionally, yes. Because the - 
the musical friend was always very close to me, I was always very friendly with him, in fact the whole family. The - the - one brother and one, two, three - four sisters. And they all played. And they each played a different instrument. And then of course
 - another thing we had in those days was the Saturday night concerts at the Victoria Hall and the Kings Hall. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8847505\charrsid1986722 
And these very, very popular indeed - they might have a bit of cinema which wasn't very good and people to sing and entertain and - the price was reasonable, tuppence. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 
And there were several well known entertainers. I know there was one family, Sefton Cross and his boy and girl who used to - give very good entertainment. He was a cartoonist and the girl was very clever at - tearing paper and the boy
 had his own tricks and they were always very well turned out and they were very popular. The daughter is at present a neighbour of mine and I see her occasionally. They used to take part in - they were a professional turn which used to take part in these
 - concerts, sometimes, Saturday evening concerts. And then we had several other local entertainers who - became more or less famous. Terry and Tony Wilson who used to sing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2491144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 There was quite a lot going in Bolton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5519484 BT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1590276\charrsid1986722 Oh yes, quite a lot. And then had
 our own local authors. Allen Clarke. Was very well know. His brother, Tom Clarke, was a great friend of my brother's and he became a very well known journalist. I remember him coming home when he covered the - telling us all about it when he covered the 
Russo-Japanese war for the Manchester Guardian.
\par }}